SUMMARY:Plyometrics + Functional Power
DESCRIPTION:Overview:\nMacros: 3550 kcal\, 165 g protein\, 520 g carbs\, 1
 00 g fat\nCategory: sprint\nRun volume: 3 km\nAdjustments:\n- Adjusted fo
 r schedule constraints.\n\nWarm-Up:\n- 10 min easy plus skips\, ankling\,
  hip openers\, and 3 relaxed strides.\n\nMain Work:\n- Progression: add p
 ower volume only when jumps stay crisp and knees stay quiet the next day\
 ; sprint RPE 7-8. Reduce volume by 25-40% before adding intensity.\n- Ply
 ometrics: pogos 3 x 20 sec\, low broad jumps 4 x 2\, and med-ball slams 4
  x 5 at crisp RPE 6-7 if available.\n- Hill sprint technique: 4-6 x 8-10 
 sec at sprint RPE 7-8.\n- Functional work: sled push if easy to set up or
  farmer carries 4 x 30 m at RPE 7.\n- Core: crawling 3 x 20 m or dead bug
  3 x 8 per side.\n\nRun:\n- Planned running volume: 3 km.\n\nFueling:\n- 
 Hit daily macros\, keep protein near target\, and place carbohydrates bef
 ore and after training.\n\nRecovery:\n- Sleep window stays 22:00-06:00\; 
 add mobility if joints feel stiff.
